sub_title: Project Manager at Orion Business Innovation
summary:
Lokesh is a graduate from Fordham Universities Gabelli School of Business. He graduated with a Bachelor of Science degree in finance with a secondary concentration in Financial Technology. He has a diverse work experience background in the private technology space having worked on both the delivery/transformation and financial side of private technology companies. 

Lokesh's work experience in the private technology space started off at Manhattan Venture Partners, a highly specialized Investment Bank focuses solely on the "Secondary Direct Venture Market" - negotiating and arranging for the purchase and transfer of private securities in later stage, venture capital financed, "Pre-IPO" technology companies on a global basis. Some of Manhattan Venture Partner's historical Pre-IPO equity transactions include purchasing shares of Lyft, Facebook, Alibaba, Spotify, and Palantir at discounts to their current and/or eventual IPO valuations. He then transitioned into a M&A analyst role at Orion Business Innovation, a global technology services firm focused on enterprise digital transformation. Orion is a One Equity Partners (OEP) investment platform company, for OEP to invest in the digital transformation space. As an M&A analyst at a private technology company, he has worked on multiple private technology acquisition deals which has grown his knowledge on the financial side of the space. 

He then accepted a larger role within Orion as a Junior Business Analyst more focused on digital transformation delivery to Orion's clients. In the Junior Business Analyst position, Lokesh has gained tremendous knowledge and unique insight into digital transformation. From the Junior Business Analyst position, Lokesh was able to grow through experiencing the different roles and realities of a front facing resources. He started off as the third analyst under two other senior analysts building a partnership tax platform using agile methodology. Through this experience he was able to learn best practices for requirements gathering, Dev Ops management, writing product requirement documents, writing business requirement documents, client reporting, stakeholder management, and internal resource management. After successfully delivering for the client, Lokesh then took on the task of managing the operations, financials, and key reporting for a new account that was relatively small at the time. Fast forward to 2022, the same account is one of the largest in the company with over 200+ resources across 5 Orion delivery centers (India, Serbia, Turkey, Mexico, America) on 10+ projects.

email_text:
Dear Lokesh, 

I hope the new year is treating you well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a sophomore studying finance and accounting at NYU Stern. I would like to know your availability for a quick chat in the coming weeks to hear about your experience at Orion Business Innovation, particularly the path that led you to project management from M&A advisory. 

As someone unsure of the best way to start a career in project management, advice from someone with such a diverse background would be invaluable. I'd love to learn more about how you successfully manage a team across five continents and your experience working with EY on digital tax transformations. 

I am attaching my resume for you to look over, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that works for you. Thank you for considering my request, and I am excited to hear from you. 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

email_text:
Dear Steven, 

I hope you're doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a junior at NYU Stern studying finance and accounting. I'm inquiring if you are available for a quick call in the coming weeks to discuss your experience at the intersection of strategy consulting and change management. 

As someone unsure of the best way to start a career in strategy consulting, advice from someone with so much experience would be amazing. I'd love to learn more about your experience at KPMG and why you chose management consulting after studying finance and music. 

Your insights would be especially beneficial as someone interested in the intersection of tech and consulting on exploring how firms best adapt to a rapidly changing environmentóhearing about your journey from conducting research at Stern to working at KPMG. 

I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that fits. I look forward to connecting and hope you have a great rest of your week! 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

summary:
‚Ä¢ Experienced Finance, Strategy, Banking (US-public institutions), Technology, and Regulatory compliance professional.
‚Ä¢ Planning and budgeting
‚Ä¢ CFA II (candidate) 

MBA, Finance & Strategy. Expertise in transformation for Banking and Capital Markets, Financial Institutions: Technologies, Operations, Real Assets, Digital, M&A.

Leadership

Communication. Top-down approach. Problem statements. Vision and values framing. Project lead.

Business Problems Solving

Framing and Problem Definition, Data Gathering & Analysis, Communication of Recommendation & Design Thinking, Social & International Investments.

Data Analytics

Programming for time series and cross-sectional analysis (Python, R environments), ARIMA, SARIMA, Fitted Model, Forecasting, Box-Ljung test, OLS Regression, Multiple regression, Non-linear regression, Linear Probability Model, Probit and Logit.

Modeling with spreadsheet, Monte-Carlo Sensitivity, Clustering model, Tornado Charts, Spreadsheet Engineering, Sensitivity Analysis, Linear, Non-Linear and Uncertainty Optimization, Sensitivity, Constraints (network, binary), Variable Distribution Selection, Decision trees, Clustering.

Finance

Capital Budgeting, Bond Pricing, Equity Valuation, Portfolio Valuation, Diversification, Trade-off Theory, Modigliani Miller Theory, Incremental Cash Flow Effects, Elasticity, Agency Problems, Information Asymmetry, Trade Credit, WACC, APV, DTS, Capital Raising theory, Residual Income Valuation, Forecasting Financial Statements, Price determination, Game theory.

Capital IQ, OLS regressions, ARIMA time-series model, K-NN-ANN method, Python, Financial-statement analysis, Event-study methodology, Portfolio evaluation, Monte Carlo simulations, Stochastic analysis.

Corporate Governance

Delaware courts rules, ESG, Agency and Dual Agency Evaluation, US Corporations, Roundtable Stakeholders Models, Strategy in Perfect Models, Voting, International Shareholder Rights, Integrity, Board Composition and Governance.

Financial Technologies

ERP Systems, Real Options, Blockchain, Encryptions and Hashing, AoN Diagrams, Pivot Table, Tableau Visualization, Network Effect, Access Database, Information Value, Relational Databases, VBA and multi-variable problem solving, Data-mining, Quantum Computing, Law of: US Security law (Howey test).

Accounting

Audit, Taxation, Consolidation, Adjustments, Chronology, M&A, Inter-corporate Investments, Outside Interests, Statutory merger, FX Transactions, Inter-company Transactions, Re-measurement, Translations, Hedging, 338 tax election, GAAP.

‚Ä¢ Associations: projects dev., tech.

Dear Maxime, 

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a junior at NYU Stern studying finance and accounting. I am particularly interested in strategy consulting. Would you be free for a call or coffee in the coming weeks to discuss your experience at KPMG helping firms strategize, optimize, and reimagine their operating models? 

As someone still discovering the best way to start a career in the field, advice from someone with so much experience would be invaluable. I would love to learn more about how strategy consulting adapted to the pandemic and evolved in the face of new challenges during that time. 

I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I look forward to hearing from you soon. 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

Pranjay Kumar

email_text:
Dear Aditi, 

Happy New Year, and I hope you have a fantastic start to the year! 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a sophomore concentrating in finance and accounting at Stern. I am inquiring about your availability for a quick call in the coming weeks to hear about your experience at Accenture and why you chose a career in management consulting. 

As someone unsure of the best way to start a career in consulting, advice from someone with so much experience would be amazing. I'd love to learn about some of Accenture's amazing work and how it ties Stakeholder Management into its operations as an advisor. 

I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that fits. A shared Stern and New Jersey background makes your advice and guidance even more significant for me. 

I look forward to hearing from you, and hope you have a great rest of your week! 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

sub_title: Senior Analyst @ Accenture | NYU Stern Grad
summary:
As a Senior Analyst at Accenture, I work with clients across various industries to help them solve their most complex business challenges and achieve their strategic goals. With my experience in both finance and consulting, I leverage my critical thinking, data analysis, and teamwork skills to collaborate effectively with diverse stakeholders. My focus lies in delivering innovative, data-driven solutions that create value and a lasting impact for our clients. 

I graduated from NYU Stern School of Business with a BS in Business, concentrating in Finance and Management. I also minored in Entertainment Business, reflecting my passion for the Media & Entertainment industry. During my studies, I participated in multiple academic and extracurricular activities that enhanced my leadership and teamwork skills. This included a transformative experience studying abroad in Prague, where I gained exposure to diverse cultures and viewpoints. Furthermore, my contributions as a Work-Study Intern in the Management & Organizations Department at NYU Stern allowed me to support vital research and teaching, particularly in areas such as leadership, diversity, and ethics.

Driven by my enthusiasm for continuous learning, collaborative teamwork, and creating positive change, I am deeply committed to making a meaningful impact in every endeavor I undertake.

Dear Linna, 

I hope you're doing great. 

I am Pranjay Kumar, currently in my sophomore year, majoring in accounting and finance. Your impressive profile on LinkedIn, especially your work in sustainability consulting and business strategy at Accenture, caught my eye. 

I am just contacting you to ask for your insights and experiences in these dynamic fields. Would you be open to having a coffee chat in the coming weeks? I am particularly keen to understand how Accenture integrates sustainability into its business strategies and how consultants like yourself navigate these challenges. 

Your expertise in delivering CRM and ESG solutions for top-tier financial services and tech firms is precisely the experience I aspire to gain. As I navigate my career path, your perspective could provide invaluable guidance. 

I have attached my resume for you to look over. Please let me know a time that works best for you; I am more than willing to accommodate your schedule. 

Thank you very much for considering my request. I look forward to learning from your journey and gaining insights that can shape my future in the industry. 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

Pranjay Kumar

sub_title: Digital Business Transformation, Growth Strategy | Accenture
summary:
A modern, forward looking financial services leader with over 30+ years of broad and deep experience in consumer and commercial banking including retail banking, personal wealth management, credit cards, payments and insurance.  I lead organizations through end to end Digital Business Transformations, Marketing Modernizations, and Modern Product Management evolutions -- all which require holistically connecting and executing a set of customer-centric business strategies (leveraging design thinking, service design, Journey mapping, martech, CX, Voice of Customer, Segmentation) to transform how business processes, customer journeys, and data in the front, middle and back office are redesigned to impact both operational efficiency and net new growth. 

I am also a proven Growth and Innovation executive that helps organizations identify growth strategies in their core business along with exploring new adjacent and disruptive spaces. Leading with both human centered design and classic management consulting techniques, I lead cross functional teams to seed concepts in the market place, demonstrate commercial value, and test with real users. I then drive downstream GTM marketing execution inclusive of leveraging Martech to drive higher orders of personalization to maximize adoption, customer engagement and monetization. Ultimately, with the aim of scaling, building valuation and driving a liquidity event. I also lead strategic and financial due diligence to explore build, buy, partner pathways to max ROI. 

A fierce advocate of diversity, equity and inclusion, I work passionately to realize the promise of diversity within my own organization, and my client teams. 
           
Next-gen strategies: Growth Strategy, Organic and Inorganic growth, Agile Operating Models, CX Strategies, Product Innovation, DevOps + DesignOps, Product Management, Value Propositions, Test&Learn, Customer Engagement, Ventures, Growth and Innovation, Liquidity event

email_text:
Dear Rina, 

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am pursuing a degree in Accounting and Finance. Having discovered your profile on LinkedIn, I was immediately drawn to your extensive experience in digital business transformation and growth strategy at Accenture. Your journey, especially your consumer and commercial banking work, is impressive and inspirational. 

I am particularly intrigued by how you have led organizations through significant digital transformations and modern product management evolutions. As I am keenly interested in this domain, I would greatly appreciate the opportunity to learn from someone of your expertise. 

Would you be available for a brief coffee chat shortly? I am eager to hear about your experiences, particularly how you integrate customer-centric business strategies and leverage design thinking and service design in your role. 

I understand your schedule might be tight, but I would be more than willing to adjust to your convenience. I have attached my resume and look forward to gaining insights from your career journey. 

Thank you for considering my request, and I hope we can set up a meeting soon. 

Best regards, 

Pranjay Kumar

Dear Ruhani, 

Happy New Year, and I hope your year is off to a fantastic start! 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a sophomore studying finance and accounting. I'd like to know your availability for a quick call or coffee in the coming weeks to hear about your experience at Accenture in marketing transformation consulting and your journey transitioning from digital consulting. 

As someone unsure of the best way to start a career in consulting, advice from someone with so much experience would be amazing. I'd love to learn more about how you created and pitched a software company with a $6 million valuation for Accenture Song. 

I look forward to hearing from you and hope you have a great rest of your week!

Pranjay Kumar

summary:
Digital Marketing professional with 12 years experience managing online consumer marketing strategy for global brands (Accenture, PayPal, American Express, Time Inc). My focus is in multi-channel digital marketing journeys and acquiring new customer base. Areas of expertise include: digital marketing strategy, email marketing, customer/user acquisition marketing, direct marketing, testing & optimization, e-commerce, campaign and on-site analytics, newsletters, Search Engine Marketing (SEM), Search Engine Optimization (SEO), direct mail, print, multivariate testing, online audience development, business development, social media marketing, web analytics (Google Analytics), and monetization of digital content.

email_text:
Hello Melanie, 

Happy New Year! I hope it's off to a great start for you. 

I'm Pranjay Kumar, a sophomore at NYU Stern majoring in finance and accounting. I'm reaching out to explore the possibility of having a brief chat or coffee meet-up in the next few weeks. I'm keen to learn about your journey from Stern to a career in consulting at Accenture. 

Besides my studies, I'm deeply interested in open-source AI development and am currently involved in a research project at Stern focused on enhancing the empathy of chatbots. Given my aspirations in AI consulting, your insights and experiences would be incredibly helpful. I'm particularly interested in how Accenture navigates the dynamic landscape of artificial intelligence in its client advisories. 

I have attached my resume for you to look over. I'm flexible and can adjust your schedule for a convenient meeting time. I look forward to discussing this further with you. 

I wish you a wonderful week ahead! 

Best regards, 
Pranjay Kumar

summary:
I am a Senior Manager at Accenture, with over 18 years of experience in sales and operations.  My core competencies include supply chain optimization, logistics management, and freight payment and audit services.

My objective is to help clients achieve their business goals and optimize their supply chain performance through a value-based sales approach. I collaborate across the organization to provide valuable resources and solutions for our client base, ranging from large e-commerce retailers to global manufacturers. I have also consulted operational and technical advancements, and negotiated and secured business agreements with strong ROIs. I am passionate about leadership and team development, and strive to empower, motivate, and inspire my team and peers.

email_text:
Dear Eddie, 

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a sophomore studying finance and accounting at NYU Stern. I am writing this email to inquire about your availability for a quick call or coffee in the coming weeks. 

As someone still navigating the uncertainties of starting a career in the finance industry, advice from someone with so much expertise would be invaluable. I'd love to hear about your journey, especially how you transitioned from finance to consulting and why. In particular, I am interested in the intersection of finance and technology, discussing how growth strategies differ in the digital age would be fascinating. 

I have attached my resume for your reference, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that fits. I look forward to talking with you, and thank you for considering my request. 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

email_text:
Dear Paola, 

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a sophomore at NYU Stern studying Finance and Accounting. I was wondering if you have a few minutes to connect in the coming weeks for a quick call. 

I am unsure about the career path in finance. However, your experience in life sciences consulting, starting as an analyst at Accenture in NY and becoming a strategy consultant, would be insightful. I would love to hear about the journey from New York to Toronto and why you made such a big move. I am particularly interested in understanding how AI and data analytics influence your strategy projects. 

I've attached my resume for you to look over, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that fits. Please let me know if there is a beneficial time for you or if you prefer to coordinate through a LinkedIn message. 

I look forward to hearing from you and hopefully getting to connect! 

Best, 
Pranjay Kumar

email_text:
Dear Sasha, 

I hope the new year is treating you well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a junior studying finance and accounting at NYU Stern. I would like to inquire about your availability for a quick call or coffee in the coming weeks to hear more about your journey at Accenture and why you came to marketing consultancy from undergrad. 

As someone unsure of the best way to start a career in management consulting, advice from someone with so much experience would be amazing. I'd love to learn how you've seen the marketing landscape change and what your thoughts are on its direction. 

I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that fits. I look forward to hearing from you and hope you have a great rest of your week! 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

Dear Demetris, 

I hope you're doing well and staying healthy. 

I am Pranjay Kumar, a sophomore in the BS/MS program at Stern, specializing in finance and accounting. I would like to hear your thoughts and guidance. Your journey at Alvarez & Marzel intrigues me, particularly your transition into International Tax post-college. 

As I navigate my path toward completing my CPA, I ponder the myriad career opportunities available. Your experience and knowledge could give me a much-needed perspective in this context. I am particularly interested in understanding your collegiate journey and how it shaped your professional life. 

Being actively engaged in the Stern Accounting Society and passionate about writing, I immensely value advice from a seasoned professional like yourself. It would be a great honor to have a brief conversation with you over a call or a coffee in the coming weeks to delve deeper into your experiences. 

I've attached my resume here for you to look over. I'm excited to talk with you and am hopeful for a positive response. 

Warm regards, 

Pranjay Kumar

Dear Claire, 

I hope you're doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a sophomore at NYU Stern studying finance and accounting. I wanted to inquire about your availability for a quick chat in the coming weeks to hear about your experience at BCG and why you came to consulting from investment banking. 

As someone unsure of the best way to start a career in consulting, advice from someone with so much experience would be amazing. In particular, I'd love to learn more about your experience starting Prado and Spark and what these enterprises taught you. 

I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that fits. I look forward to hearing from you and hope you have a great rest of your week! 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

I am just writing to ask about your availability for a quick call or coffee in the next few weeks. I would love to hear about your experience at Deloitte and learn why you decided to switch from teaching to consulting.

I have attached my resume for you to look over and am happy to work around your schedule to find a convenient time for us to connect. I look forward to hearing from you soon and hope you have a great rest of your day! 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

As someone still exploring their career path, advice from someone with so much experience would be amazing. I am particularly interested in how ESG advisory is becoming a more significant part of the finance industry, and I'd love to learn more about your experiences in that space. 

I have attached my resume for your reference. Please let me know what time works well for you, and I will gladly work around your schedule. I look forward to hearing from you and hope you have a great rest of your week! 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

summary:
Keven Shang is a Senior Consultant at FTI Consulting and is based in New York, NY. 

Keven is in the Office of the CFO Solutions practice in the Company's Corporate Finance segment. He is a corporate finance and management consulting professional, and is experienced in FP&A, Carve-Outs, Finance System Implementations, Finance Transformation and Cost Optimization.

During his time in NYU, Keven earned his degree in Business, concentrating in Finance and Data Science. He was a student-athlete on NYU's Men's Varsity Swim Team for three years. In his free time, he enjoys cooking, running, biking, music production, and playing the ukulele.

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

sub_title: Forensic Accountant | Consulting and Testifying Expert | Investigations | Litigation Support
summary:
I have nearly 20 years of experience in forensic accounting.  I conduct investigations and provide expert/consulting services in areas including fraud, complex financial analyses, false claims, accounting irregularities and human trafficking. I conduct damage calculations and serve as an expert witness on subject matters.  I have issued expert reports, provided deposition testimony and testified at trial.  

I have spoken on multiple panels on topics including accounting, investigations and human trafficking.  In connection with my pro-bono activities, I was recognized by the Human Trafficking Legal Center as its Advocate of the Year in 2021. sub_title: Senior Managing Director at FTI Consulting
summary:
Matthew Diaz is a Senior Managing Director in FTI Consulting's Corporate Finance/Restructuring practice.  Mr. Diaz has been with FTI since 2005 and in that time has assisted key stakeholders in over 40 distressed situations.  Prior to joining FTI, Mr. Diaz worked as the Restructuring Director at Impath, where he was brought in to restate the Company's books and records after the identification of accounting irregularities and to help prepare it for sale.  Additionally, Mr. Diaz served as the Chief Financial Officer at Graham Field Inc. where he raised replacement DIP financing and facilitated the sale of the company. 

Since joining FTI, Mr. Diaz has been in FTI's Creditor Rights practice and through the representation of various key stakeholders has restructured numerous organizations including Cengage Learning, Hawker Beechcraft, TerreStar Networks, Smurfit Stone, Chemtura Corporation, Buffets, Bally's Total Fitness, and Calpine Corporation.

Mr. Diaz holds an M.B.A. with a concentration in finance and management from Columbia Business School and a B.S. in accounting and finance from the Leonard N. Stern School of Business at New York University. He is a Certified Insolvency and Restructuring Advisor, a Certified Turnaround Professional and a Certified Public Accountant.  Most recently, Mr. Diaz was recognized as a winner of The M&A Advisor‚Äôs 5th Annual 40 Under 40 Awards in the Service Provider category, which recognizes leading professionals in the mergers and acquisitions, financing and turnaround professions.

email_text:
Dear Matt, 

I hope you had a great start to the New Year! 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a sophomore studying finance and accounting at the Stern School of Business, concentrating on becoming a CPA. I wanted to inquire about your availability for a quick call or coffee to learn more about your experience in consulting and your transition from corporate finance to FTI Consulting as a Managing Director overseeing the restructuring group 

As someone unsure of the best way to begin a career in financial advisory, advice from someone with so much knowledge and experience would be amazing! In particular, I am interested in understanding the impact of emerging technology on financial strategy and operations. 

I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that fits. I look forward to hearing from you and hope you have a great week! 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

Best regards, 
Pranjay Kumar

sub_title: Managing Director Business Transformation & Transactions | Human Capital
summary:
For the last 20+ years I have been fortunate to provide corporate and consultant leadership in compensation and benefits, mergers & acquisitions, change management, and strategic human resources. My background includes experience at Fortune 1000 public companies and consulting for marquis human capital firms. I led numerous human resources strategic initiatives, designed, negotiated and managed a full range of compensation and benefit programs, oversaw HR implications of M&As, designed and implemented change management strategy, led strong teams and managed large scale global client engagements.

I am a Fellow of the Society of Actuaries (FSA), an Enrolled Actuary (EA), and a member of WorldatWork (CCP and CECP).

Highlights

Compensation and Benefits: Broad experience from day-to-day administration to strategic design for executive and sales team and working with Board Compensation Committees. Focused on developing compensation and benefit programs to engage employees and address a wide range of business and people issues.

Mergers & Acquisitions: Extensive experience with acquisitions and divestitures. Resolve challenging issues to keep deals moving. Develop and implement long and short-term strategies to integrate HR structures, compensation and benefit programs, union and non-union labor strategies, and change of control and severance agreements. 

Change Management: Led cross-functional teams to develop and deliver training and communication to educate leaders, managers and employees to adapt and embrace change. Built and implemented strategy to engage employees for wide spectrum of organizational changes ranging from merger integration, system conversions, and changes with compensation and benefits programs.

Strategic Human Resources: Teamed with HR business partners, executive leadership, and finance to collaborate and address strategic and on-going business issues. Worked across functions and gained experience on a range of HR initiatives.

Best regards, 
Pranjay Kumar

summary:
I love working with amazing people. I relish the challenges that come with consulting and working with diverse projects and clients because, in my eyes, learning never ceases. Throughout my career as a consultant, I've had the privilege of collaborating with incredibly talented people who've enriched my knowledge and experience.

My journey has always been guided by a profound interest in the worlds of finance and strategy. I'm committed to meticulous analysis, exhaustive market research, and the gathering of competitive intelligence to drive data-driven recommendations. What drives me each morning is the chance to engineer inventive, enduring, and pragmatic solutions that tackle complex business challenges head-on while enhancing operational efficiency. 

Professional success, in my view, transcends mere numbers and strategies; it's fundamentally about people and the relationships we build. Drawing from my experiences as both a mentor and a mentee, I hold a deep commitment to fostering an inclusive environment where each individual can excel and fully realize their potential.

When I'm not immersed in client work, you'll find me advancing the mission of Rock-Rising, a non-profit media production company. Here, I've not only built business plans and financial forecasts but also woven my strategic vision to propel this organization to the best of my abilities. My connection to Rock-Rising runs deep, rooted in my love for New York City and a profound admiration for the artists who flourish in this vibrant arena.

email_text:
Dear Udit, 

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a junior studying finance and accounting at NYU Stern. I am just contacting you to ask about your availability for a brief call or meeting in the upcoming weeks. I am keen to learn about your experience at KPMG and the transition from a long stint in strategy operations and supply chain management to consulting. 

As someone uncertain about the best approach to enter the field of strategy consulting, your insights, given your extensive experience, would be incredibly valuable. I am eager to understand how your graduate degree at NYU Stern has shaped your approach to strategy consulting. 

I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I am willing to coordinate with your schedule to find a suitable time. I look forward to your response and hope you have a great week! 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

summary:
‚Ä¢ Experienced Finance, Strategy, Banking (US-public institutions), Technology, and Regulatory compliance professional.
‚Ä¢ Planning and budgeting
‚Ä¢ CFA II (candidate) 

MBA, Finance & Strategy. Expertise in transformation for Banking and Capital Markets, Financial Institutions: Technologies, Operations, Real Assets, Digital, M&A.

Leadership

Communication. Top-down approach. Problem statements. Vision and values framing. Project lead.

Business Problems Solving

Framing and Problem Definition, Data Gathering & Analysis, Communication of Recommendation & Design Thinking, Social & International Investments.

Data Analytics

Programming for time series and cross-sectional analysis (Python, R environments), ARIMA, SARIMA, Fitted Model, Forecasting, Box-Ljung test, OLS Regression, Multiple regression, Non-linear regression, Linear Probability Model, Probit and Logit.

Modeling with spreadsheet, Monte-Carlo Sensitivity, Clustering model, Tornado Charts, Spreadsheet Engineering, Sensitivity Analysis, Linear, Non-Linear and Uncertainty Optimization, Sensitivity, Constraints (network, binary), Variable Distribution Selection, Decision trees, Clustering.

Finance

Capital Budgeting, Bond Pricing, Equity Valuation, Portfolio Valuation, Diversification, Trade-off Theory, Modigliani Miller Theory, Incremental Cash Flow Effects, Elasticity, Agency Problems, Information Asymmetry, Trade Credit, WACC, APV, DTS, Capital Raising theory, Residual Income Valuation, Forecasting Financial Statements, Price determination, Game theory.

Capital IQ, OLS regressions, ARIMA time-series model, K-NN-ANN method, Python, Financial-statement analysis, Event-study methodology, Portfolio evaluation, Monte Carlo simulations, Stochastic analysis.

Corporate Governance

Delaware courts rules, ESG, Agency and Dual Agency Evaluation, US Corporations, Roundtable Stakeholders Models, Strategy in Perfect Models, Voting, International Shareholder Rights, Integrity, Board Composition and Governance.

Financial Technologies

ERP Systems, Real Options, Blockchain, Encryptions and Hashing, AoN Diagrams, Pivot Table, Tableau Visualization, Network Effect, Access Database, Information Value, Relational Databases, VBA and multi-variable problem solving, Data-mining, Quantum Computing, Law of: US Security law (Howey test).

Accounting

Audit, Taxation, Consolidation, Adjustments, Chronology, M&A, Inter-corporate Investments, Outside Interests, Statutory merger, FX Transactions, Inter-company Transactions, Re-measurement, Translations, Hedging, 338 tax election, GAAP.

email_text:
Dear Maxime, 

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a junior at NYU Stern studying finance and accounting. I am particularly interested in strategy consulting. Would you be free for a call or coffee in the coming weeks to discuss your experience at KPMG helping firms strategize, optimize, and reimagine their operating models? 

As someone still discovering the best way to start a career in the field, advice from someone with so much experience would be invaluable. I would love to learn more about how strategy consulting adapted to the pandemic and evolved in the face of new challenges during that time. 

I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I look forward to hearing from you soon. 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

Our team works together with the KPMG colleagues in Audit and Valuation services to cover all relevant aspects of these changes in financial reporting requirements.

email_text:
Dear Jaime, 

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a junior studying finance and accounting at NYU Stern. I am figuring out what I want to do post-graduation, and your experience in KPMG Deal Advisory and Strategy intrigued me. Would you have time for a call in the coming weeks to discuss your experience at KPMG and how you've seen the industry change over the years? 

As someone unsure of the best way to start a career in strategy consulting, advice from someone with so much experience would be amazing. I'd love to learn more about your experience coming from a background in accounting and how that has influenced your approach to strategy consulting. 

I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that fits. I look forward to hearing from you and hope you have a great rest of your week! 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

summary:
As a Strategy Associate at KPMG US, I leverage a unique blend of creative flair and analytical precision to support management in crafting compelling presentations for clients spanning diverse industries, such as Consumer Retail, Healthcare, and Entertainment. This includes conducting and synthesizing complex financial and operational analyses to provide insights.
 
I graduated with a Master of Science in Accounting and a Bachelor's degree in Business with a minor in English and American Literature from NYU Stern School of Business, where I achieved Summa Cum Laude, Dean's List, and Founder's Day honors. My role as a teaching fellow within Stern Business School was my most fulfilling experience during my time at NYU. I worked in the role for 2 years within the Organizational Communications and Business Communications departments for undergraduates and MBA students respectively.

email_text:
Dear Alan, 

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a junior at NYU Stern studying Finance and Accounting. I am interested in exploring strategy consulting and learning about your experience at KPMG, particularly in the strategy practice. 

I find your experience in combining strategy and technology at KPMG intriguing. As someone learning about its impact at the intersection of data, finance, and strategy, I'd love to hear about some of the challenges or exciting projects you've encountered. 

I'd greatly appreciate the opportunity to connect with you for a quick call or coffee in the coming weeks to hear about your experience and journey. I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a convenient time. 

I look forward to connecting with you and hope you have a great rest of your week. 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

sub_title: Program Management / Project Management / Strategy / Transformation / Operations
summary:
Results-driven, accomplished, and high-performing Program/Project Manager Professional with 20 years of experience delivering global business solutions to Fortune 500, startups, and private equity owned organizations in various industries. Dedicated to managing initiatives that bring strategies, efficiencies, and transformation into alignment with present and future client‚Äôs business goals. 

Recognized and empowering leader with keen business acumen, continuous improvement, and problem-solving expertise, a genuine influencer uniquely qualified to liaise all stakeholders with the ability to readily translate vision into actionable, value-added results.

People & Program Leader: Strengthens people, process and performance by defining and leading projects and programs to execute on strategic goals.

Relationship Builder: Partners with cross-functional teams and stakeholders to strategize ideas and build consensus.  Navigates team dynamics to foster stronger cultures and improved operations.

Strategic Advisor: Counsels executive leaders and influences decisions around strategy, initiatives, organizational design, efficiencies, transformation and organization.

Dear Karen, 

I hope you're doing well. My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a junior studying finance and accounting at NYU Stern. 

Given your extensive career in strategy and transformation, I am keen to hear about your experiences at KPMG and in establishing your consulting practice in Atlanta. Your wealth of knowledge and experience at top consulting firms is something I am eager to learn from. 

I'd like to know how you've seen changes in strategy and consulting practices over the years, especially in light of the digital revolution and its impact on clients' decision-making. I would appreciate the opportunity to arrange a meeting whenever you have time, whether a brief call or a coffee, to gain insight into your journey. 

I have enclosed my resume for you to look over. Thank you for considering my request, and I am excited to hear back from you. 

Warm regards, 
Pranjay Kumar

sub_title: Data Strategy Lead @ KPMG US | MBA, ESG
summary:
As a data strategist in the Advisory Data Organization at KPMG US, I leverage my 15+ years of experience in data and project management to help clients and organizations optimize their data assets and achieve their strategic goals. I have a MBA from NYU Stern and a Master of Information from Rutgers University, as well as multiple certifications in project management, sustainable finance, and data analytics.

My core competencies include data analysis, strategy, knowledge management, and communication. I have successfully led and delivered data-driven projects for various industries and sectors, including management consulting, education, and finance. I have also developed and implemented data governance, quality, and security frameworks and standards for internal and external stakeholders. My mission is to empower data-driven decision-making and innovation, and to create value and impact for clients and society.

Dear Katie, 

I hope this email finds you well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a junior at NYU Stern, studying finance and accounting. I am writing to express my interest in learning more about the strategy consulting field and your experience at KPMG. 

Given my passion for literature and data, I am interested in how KPMG brings together data and strategy to provide value to its clients. I'd love to hear about your experience at KPMG as an Advisory Data Strategy Lead, especially how you have seen the role of data strategy evolve in a post-pandemic world. 

I have attached my resume for your reference, and I would greatly appreciate the opportunity to learn from your experience and advice with a quick call or coffee chat. Please let me know if there's a time that works for you, and I will gladly work around your schedule. 

Thank you for considering my request. I look forward to hearing from you and hope you have a great rest of your week. 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

sub_title: Strategy | M&A | Transformation | Leadership | Business Building
summary:
A transformation expert, business builder, and corporate strategist with extensive experience in mergers & acquisitions, delivering change, operations, revenue growth, and cost optimization.

I help start-up, bulge-bracket, and financial services organizations deliver change that facilitates growth, profitability, and sustainability. As a partner at IM2 Consulting and during my time at both PwC and KPMG, I helped grow businesses, led talented teams, and delivered innovative solutions for our clients' most complex and critical challenges. 

With experience in delivering new products, market entry, problem solving, solution design, performance improvement, operating models, transactions, strategy, and corporate initiatives, I have achieved nearly a billion dollars in operational improvements for my clients and facilitated over $38 billion in M&A transactions.

Dear Brian, 

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a junior at NYU Stern studying finance and accounting. I am keenly interested in strategy consulting and would like to inquire about your availability for a brief call in the upcoming weeks. I want to discuss your experience and seek advice as someone aspiring to begin a career in strategy consulting. 

Your career journey from leading IM2 Consulting in NYC to your current position at KPMG is awe-inspiring, and I am eager to learn more about how you established your career in strategy consulting. Specifically, with your extensive experience advising large companies on M&A deals and corporate development strategy, I would like to understand your perspective on the evolving impact of M&A in the tech and finance industries over the next few years. Also, I would like your advice for someone pursuing a career in the same space.

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

email_text:
Dear Joe, 

I hope you are doing well. 

I am Pranjay Kumar, a finance and accounting junior at NYU Stern. I want to schedule a brief call at your convenience to discuss your transition from consulting to strategy at KPMG and your experience in the Salesforce arena. Your insights would be precious to me as I am still figuring out my career path. 

I have attached my resume for your reference, and I am flexible to work around your schedule. I look forward to your response and wish you a great week ahead. 

Best regards, 
Pranjay Kumar

sub_title: Enterprise Transformation from Strategy to Execution
summary:
Nick guides global organizations on large scale transformations from strategy through execution, bringing business and technology together. He is a seasoned management and technology professional with over 17 years of consulting/advisory experience for top global banks, asset management and insurance institutions, he has also helped clients setup PMO organizations from the ground up to manage their portfolio of programs/projects totaling over $500 million USD. 

Nick is based in NYC, he is well versed in working with international cultures having worked in the UK, Canada, Japan, Dubai, Hong Kong and across the US.


Specialties: 
‚Ä¢Advisory/Consulting - Management and Technology Consulting, CIO & CTO Advisory
‚Ä¢Large Scale Transformation - Operation, Technology and Regulatory
‚Ä¢Management - PMO, Center of Excellence, Resource and Financials
‚Ä¢Large scale transformations
‚Ä¢Capital Markets System Implementations
‚Ä¢Calypso Trading System Specialist
‚Ä¢Software Development Life Cycle
‚Ä¢Fixed Income and Derivatives
‚Ä¢Trade Life Cycle, Front to Back
‚Ä¢Java, C++, Oracle, OOAD

email_text:
Dear Nick, 

I hope you're doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a junior at NYU Stern majoring in finance & accounting, originally from New Jersey. I am just contacting you to ask about your availability for a brief call in the coming weeks to learn about your transition from strategy consulting to strategy execution at large-scale financial services companies. 

Given your experience, I would like to hear your thoughts on how companies are implementing digital solutions in their strategies post-pandemic. As someone still determining the best way to begin a career in strategy consulting post-graduation, advice from someone with a lot of experience would be incredibly valuable. 

I have attached my resume for your reference, and I look forward to hearing from you. 

Warm regards, 
Pranjay Kumar

Dear Monica, 

I hope you're finding the New Year well! 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a sophomore studying finance and accounting at NYU Stern. I am interested in pursuing my CPA. I am inquiring about your availability for a quick call or coffee in the coming weeks to hear about your experience at Oliver Wyman and why you came to FP & A from auditing. As someone unsure about the best way to start a career in FP&A, advice from someone with so much experience would be amazing! 

I'd love to learn more about Oliver Wyman's interesting work in Corporate FP&A and how a seasoned professional such as yourself sees the field going in the next few years. I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I will gladly work around your schedule to find a time that fits. 

I look forward to hearing from you and hope you have a great rest of your week! 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

Dear Adejoke, 

I hope your year is off to a great start and you're staying warm in this chilly weather. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a sophomore at Stern studying finance and accounting. As someone passionate about writing and storytelling, I wanted to learn more about your experience as a writer and journalist. 

With a future aspiration in brand strategy, I was intrigued by hearing about your transition from being a writer and journalist to being a freelance social media manager. Your journey and the skillset you have developed in this field truly amaze me. 

I would love to hear more about your experience at Lippincott and what made you pursue a career in writing and storytelling after Stern. As someone still needs to figure out the best way to enter the field, advice from someone with such impressive experience would be incredible. 

I have attached my resume for you to glance over, and I would be happy to work around your schedule to find a time that fits best. I look forward to speaking with you and gaining insight from someone with such interesting experiences. 

Warm regards, 
Pranjay Kumar

sub_title: Senior Associate @ L.E.K. Consulting | Driving Growth with Innovative Strategies
summary:
As a Senior Associate at L.E.K. Consulting, I have been involved in growth strategy engagements for F500 clients, leading investment firms, and startups, across TMT, healthcare, and retail/consumer sectors. I have conducted customer interviews, developed go-to-market strategies, managed data analytics, and presented product recommendations to executive stakeholders, resulting in increased revenues, reduced user turnover, and improved customer satisfaction.

I have a strong passion for learning how businesses operate and the drivers that help them grow. I graduated from NYU Stern School of Business with a BS in Accounting and Business/Management, and a minor in Environmental Studies. I have developed product launch planning, attention to detail, and analytical skills, which I apply to my consulting projects. I am interested in business operations, strategy and operations, and data analyst roles.

Pranjay Kumar

summary:
kth300@stern.nyu.edu

I graduated from NYU Stern School of Business in 2023 with a BS in Business, where I gained a solid foundation in finance, accounting, strategy, and marketing. Since then, I have been working as an analyst at Alvarez & Marsal, a leading global professional services firm, where I provide corporate performance improvement solutions to corporate clients across various industries. I also have a passion for entrepreneurship and e-commerce, as I founded and managed my own online business to consign and resell luxury apparel, generating six-figure total revenue.

As an analyst at Alvarez & Marsal, I work with a team of experienced consultants and operators to deliver data-driven insights, actionable recommendations, and value-added outcomes for our clients. I leverage my skills in financial modeling, data analysis, market research, and project management to support various projects, such as business transformation, cost optimization, revenue enhancement, and operational excellence. I am motivated by the opportunity to learn from diverse perspectives, challenge myself with complex problems, and make a positive impact on the organizations and communities we serve. I believe that I can bring a unique combination of analytical, creative, and entrepreneurial skills to the team, as well as a global and multicultural mindset, as I speak three languages and have lived in different countries.

Dear Angelina, 

I hope you're doing well. 

I am Pranjay Kumar, a sophomore at NYU Stern studying Accounting and Finance. I wanted to inquire about your availability for a quick call in the coming weeks to hear about your experience at Alvarez & Marsal and why you came to M&A tax from law. 

As someone still exploring the many facets of a career in tax, advice from someone with such extensive experience would be invaluable. I would love to learn from your experience and better understand the differences between legal and financial career paths. I have attached my resume for your reference. 

Please let me know what time works for you, and I will gladly work around your schedule. I look forward to hearing from you and hope you have a great rest of your week! 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

email_text:
Dear Michael, 

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a sophomore at Stern studying finance and accounting. I wanted to inquire about your availability for a quick call or coffee in the coming weeks to hear about your experience at Alvarez & Marsal. 

As someone unsure of the best way to start a career in management consulting, advice from someone with so much experience would be fantastic. I'd love to learn more about your work, especially the work you do in activism, regulatory, and financial crime risks. 

I'd like to understand how you intertwined such a clearly defined career path in risk management and consulting, followed by a short stint in law, with your love of nonprofit work and social activism. As someone with a similar passion for social entrepreneurship, I'd love to learn from your experience. 

I've attached my resume for your reference, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that fits. I look forward to connecting and learning from you.

Pranjay Kumar

sub_title: Results-Driven Retail Operational Strategist | Interim C-suite Specialist | Managing Director at Alvarez & Marsal
summary:
As a Managing Director with Alvarez & Marsal's Private Equity Performance Improvement Group, I leverage my 15 years of direct retail industry experience to provide strategic solutions for existing and new business segments. My expertise lies in end-to-end product design, development, production, and sourcing optimization.

While in industry I led over 10 post-acquisition and carve-out integrations for apparel, footwear, and accessories and was responsible for operational due diligence, TSA negotiation, project planning, and seamless integration execution from merchandising to end-consumer delivery.

Most recently, I led a COGS reduction effort for a $500 million affordable luxury brand, achieving a remarkable 20 percent year-over-year reduction. This was achieved through the implementation of cost transparency, should-cost modeling, construction optimization, and factory rationalization. Additionally, I successfully led a transformation project for a $2 billion apparel retailer, streamlining their go-to-market process, reducing the calendar by 12 weeks, optimizing the assortment, and rightsizing the organization.

Additionally, I have a proven track record of driving value and operational excellence in various interim C-suite roles. 

Specializations: Post-Merger Integration |Performance Improvement| Operational Due Diligence| Carve-out | Interim Management | Retail Industry | Cost Take Out 

For more detailed information about my experience, please visit my company bio at https://www.alvarezandmarsal.com/our-people/jana-gold

Dear Ellbie,

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a sophomore majoring in finance and accounting at Stern, concentrating on CPA Track. I am writing to inquire about your availability for a quick call or coffee in the coming weeks to hear about your experience at Simon-Kucher and why you chose to pursue a career in the consulting industry after studying IO psychology. 

As someone unsure of the best way to start a career in consulting, advice from someone with so much experience would be amazing. In particular, I wanted to learn more about the Global Specialist in Learning & Development role at Simon-Kucher. 

In addition, I would love to hear about your HR Consulting experience at Bank of China and how you transitioned to Simon-Kucher. I am particularly interested in how industrial Organizational psychology can be applied in the consulting industry. 

I have attached my resume for your reference, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that fits. I look forward to hearing from you and hope you have a great rest of your week! 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

summary:
I am a Manager in the Transaction Services & Private Equity practice at Simon-Kucher, a global strategy consulting firm. In this role, I advise leading investors on growth-driven deals.

My experience includes 20+ consulting engagements involving commercial due diligence, growth strategy, pricing and packaging, and business model development. This project work has spanned multiple sectors including technology, consumer, business services, media, industrial, and financial services.

I received my MBA from the Stern School of Business at NYU and my BA from the Elliott School of International Affairs at GW.

email_text:
Dear Adam,

Happy New Year, and I hope you had a great start to 2023!

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a sophomore studying finance and accounting at NYU Stern. Would you be available for a quick call or coffee in the coming weeks to talk about your experience at Simon-Kucher and why you decided to start a career in transaction services?

As someone uncertain about the best way to start a career in transaction advisory, advice from someone with so much experience would be amazing! I'd love to learn about the most interesting projects you have worked on in your extensive career at Simon-Kucher and what led you to advise clients on commercial due diligence.

I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I would gladly work with your schedule to find a time that fits. I look forward to hearing from you and hope you have a wonderful week.

Sincerely,
Pranjay Kumar

Dear Ian, 

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a rising junior at NYU Stern majoring in finance and accounting. I am currently exploring a career in CFO Advisory and would love to learn more about your experience at Strategy&. 

I am particularly impressed by your journey from Systems Engineering at GW to Senior Associate at Strategy&. I would greatly appreciate hearing about your experience and learning from your valuable insights. 

As someone still trying to find the best way to start a career in consulting, advice from someone with so much experience would be invaluable. I would greatly appreciate the opportunity to connect in the next few weeks to hear about your career and seek guidance on navigating a career in consultancy. 

I have attached my resume for your reference. I would gladly work with your schedule to find a time that works. I look forward to connecting, and I hope you have a great rest of your week. 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

Dear Yuting,

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a rising junior at NYU Stern studying finance and accounting. I'd like to know your availability for a quick call or coffee in the coming weeks to hear about your experience as a Senior Associate at Strategy& and why you came to strategy consulting from engineering.

I am attaching my resume for you to look over. I have included my availability for a call or meeting, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that works for you. I look forward to hearing from you and hope you have a great rest of your week! 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

email_text:
Dear Spencer, 

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a rising junior studying finance and accounting at Stern. I would like to know your availability for a quick call or coffee in the coming weeks to hear more about your experience at Strategy& and why you came to consulting from a finance role at Dimensional. 

As someone trying to understand the crossover between finance and consulting, particularly in the banking industry, I find that advice from someone who has made a similar transition would be invaluable. Given their evolving digital strategy, I would love to learn more about the main challenges banks face regarding cost optimization and organizational design. 

I have attached my resume for your convenience, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that fits. I look forward to hearing from you and hope you have a great rest of your week! 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

summary:
I help firms identify and build digital capabilities to enable future growth, aligning vision, strategy, and structure.

I previously focused on ERP assessment and digital transformation, working to build value-driven IT roadmaps for customers across multiple industries. Additionally, I have applied my skills in business consulting and project management to large technology implementations in the manufacturing, oil and gas, consumer products, services, distribution, restaurants, and retail industries.   

I have recently obtained my MBA from New York University‚Äôs Stern School of Business with concentrations in Management, Strategy, and Finance. Leveraging my experience and degree, I am looking to be a valued consultative partner in crafting technology strategy to promote sustainable growth.

Dear Philip, 

I hope you're doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a rising Junior at New York University Stern studying Finance, Accounting, and Data Analysis. I would like to know a good time to connect and learn about your experience at Strategy&. 

As someone unsure of the best ways to start a career in consulting, advice from someone with so much experience would be amazing. I'd love to hear more about your journey, especially with Capgemini and the transition from consulting to business school. 

I have attached my resume for your reference. I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that works. I look forward to connecting, and I hope you have a great week! 

Best regards, 
Pranjay Kumar

Dear Adam, 

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a rising junior at Stern studying finance and accounting. I would like to know your availability for a quick call or coffee in the coming weeks to discuss your experience at Strategy& and why you came to consulting from finance and strategy at Jacmel. 

As someone still considering various career paths, advice from someone with so much experience would be excellent. I would love to know more about how you have seen the industry change over the past few years. 

I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I am happy to accommodate your schedule. Thank you for considering me, and I look forward to speaking with you soon. 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

email_text:
Dear Matthew, 

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a rising junior studying finance and accounting at NYU Stern. I'd like to know your availability for a quick call in the coming weeks to discuss your experience with strategy and why you chose to transition from operations at Anheuser-Busch to consulting. 

As someone unsure of the best way to start a career in strategy consulting with a finance background, advice from someone with so much experience would be very impactful. I'd love to learn more about how your career has focused on operational due diligence, synergy analyses, and portfolio value transformation. 

I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I would gladly accommodate your schedule. I look forward to hearing from you and hope you have a great rest of your week. 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

email_text:
Dear Lia, 

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a rising junior at Stern majoring in Finance and Accounting with an interest in TME. I would like to know your availability for a quick call or coffee in the coming weeks to discuss your experience in consulting and why you came to Strategy& from PwC. 

In particular, I would love to learn about the dynamics of the TME Strategy, where you see the industry heading in the coming years, and how Strategy& has positioned itself to take advantage of those changes. Advice from someone with so much experience would be amazing for someone considering a career in tech consulting. 

I have attached my resume for your reference. I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that works. I look forward to connecting with you and hearing about your Stern experience. 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

sub_title: Partner at Strategy& ‚ûú Enterprise Strategy through Execution | Business & Culture Transformation | US Army Veteran | West Point Graduate | NYU Stern MBA
summary:
As a Partner in Strategy&‚Äôs Enterprise Strategy & Transformation practice, I drive meaningful improvements in business value, effectiveness, and resilience. Areas of focus:

‚ûú Transforming operations to enable long-term strategy and competitive differentiators
‚ûú Driving unprecedented effectiveness
‚ûú Uncovering cost-saving opportunities and identifying reinvestment priorities
‚ûú Evolving the organizational culture to enable transformation

While I work across multiple industries, markets, and corporate structures, I bring the same core skill to every engagement: the ability to lead through challenges. That ability was cultivated early in my career as an Army operations officer deployed to some of the most dangerous areas of Iraq. 

Now, with an MBA from NYU Stern and 10+ years of strategy consulting experience, I apply those raw problem-solving and leadership abilities in complex business environments. My expertise lies in clarifying business goals, building the strategy, and then defining the processes, people, technologies, and culture necessary to execute on that strategy. 

Still strongly connected to my military roots, I continue to support servicemembers and veterans through my nonprofit organization, Service to School (https://service2school.org). Founded in 2011, we have assisted thousands in gaining admission to top academic institutions. We are able to offer these services at no cost to veterans through partnerships and sponsorships. 

Industries: Financial Services, Technology, Healthcare, Aerospace & Defense, Industrial Products, Consumer Products

Competencies: Operations & Culture Transformation, Workplace Strategy Transformation, Customer Experience Transformation, Mentoring & Coaching, Business Development, Organizational Strategy & Restructuring, Finance & HR Transformation, Strategic Business Planning, Talent Acquisition & Development, Cost Reengineering Strategy & Implementation, Manufacturing & Real Estate Optimization, Operations Management, Program Management

Dear Augusto, 

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a rising junior at NYU Stern studying finance and accounting. I want to inquire about your availability for a quick call or coffee in the coming weeks to hear about your experience at Strategy &, especially as someone making such a significant impact with so much experience. 

As someone unsure of the best way to start a career in enterprise strategy, advice from someone with so much experience would be amazing. I am particularly interested in how you have seen the field change over the years and how Strategy & is tackling these changes. 

I am attaching my resume for you to look over. I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that works. I look forward to connecting with you and hope you have a great rest of your week! 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I look forward to hearing from you soon. 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

Dear Udayan, 

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a sophomore at NYU Stern studying finance and accounting. I would like to know your availability for a quick call or coffee in the coming weeks to discuss your experience at Strategy& and why you chose to join from The World Bank. 

As someone unsure of the best way to start a career in strategy consulting, advice from someone with so much experience would be invaluable. I want to learn from your experiences in enterprise strategy, innovation, and sustainability with Strategy&, as well as your work at The World Bank for sustainable development and climate change. 

I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I would gladly accommodate your schedule and find a time that works. I look forward to connecting with you and hearing your advice. 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

summary:
Lexi is currently a manager at Strategy& (part of the PwC network) in Enterprise Strategy and Value, Pharma and Life Sciences. In her 2+ years at the firm, she has primarily served Medical Device and Diagnostics clients and has specialized in commercial growth strategy, operations transformation, and organizational change management. 

Prior to entering the class of 2021 at Stern, Lexi worked for a medical device company focused in Surgical Robotics. Over her four years with the company, her experience spanned from design engineering and data analytics to project management, all within a global, cross-functional team. 

She graduated from Bucknell University with a degree in Biomedical Engineering, where she enjoyed playing on the women‚Äôs golf team and was a leader and treasurer for the InterVarsity Christian Fellowship. In her spare time, she enjoys dancing, reading, and sharing her love of golf by teaching others.

Dear Lexi, 

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a rising junior at NYU Stern studying Finance and Accounting. I am just asking you about your availability for a brief call in early September to hear about your experience at Strategy& and how you transitioned to consulting from engineering. As someone unsure of the best way to start a career in consulting without a business background, advice from someone with so much experience is invaluable. 

Given the recent turbulence in the consulting industry, I am eager to learn about the biggest challenges you have faced as a manager and what you think the biggest drivers of change will be going forward. Considering my uncertainty about the next few years in the industry, your insights would be incredible. 

I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that fits. I look forward to hearing from you and hope you have a great rest of your week! 

Best regards, 
Pranjay Kumar

sub_title: Corporate Strategy Consultant at Strategy&, part of PwC
summary:
Zach is a Senior Associate at Strategy&, part of the PwC network, in the firm's Enterprise Strategy & Value practice. 

Prior to Strategy&, Zach was a Vice President at SIFMA, where he developed and executed engagement strategies for the trade association's members (investment banks, broker-dealers, asset managers, and service providers). 

Previously, Zach served as Associate Director of Corporate Relations at the Bipartisan Policy Center, a think tank founded by four former U.S. Senate Majority Leaders. During his tenure, Zach assisted BPC leadership in advocating bipartisan policy solutions and was a key staff member of the Health Systems Executive Council, Commission on Retirement Security and Personal Savings, American Energy Innovation Council, and the Civic Leadership Initiative. Before joining BPC, Zach was Development Assistant at the American Action Forum, an economic policy institute created by a former Director of the Congressional Budget Office. Zach's professional experience also includes positions with All Aboard Ohio, Central Ohio Symphony Orchestra, Ohio Environmental Council, and Nine-Tenths Media Group. 

Zach graduated with an MBA from NYU Stern School of Business, specializing in Strategy and Finance, and from Ohio Wesleyan University with a Bachelor of Arts, majoring in International Business. Born in Farmington, Maine and raised in Westerville, Ohio, Zach lives in Brooklyn.

email_text:
Dear Jeffrey, 

I hope you're doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I'm a rising junior at NYU Stern studying Finance and Accounting. I would like to know your availability for a quick call or coffee in the next few weeks to discuss your experience at Strategy& and why you chose to pursue a career in Tech Strategy. 

As someone unsure of the best way to start a career in Tech Strategy, advice from someone with so much experience would be invaluable. Your journey from an intern at PwC to an Associate at Strategy & makes your experience the perfect guide for someone just starting this path. 

I'd love to learn more about how Strategy and business navigate the intersection of Tech and Private Equity, as that's where I see the future of strategic consulting heading. I am particularly interested in understanding the role of Technology and Business in shaping post-acquisition organizational change. 

I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a convenient time to connect. I look forward to hearing from you and hope you have a great rest of your week! 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

sub_title: Helping B2B Companies Transform for Growth | Strategy & Operational Execution Expert
summary:
I am a highly driven professional with an strong work ethic and a continuous growth mindset. I specialize in all aspects of strategy through execution, including corporate strategy, go-to-market strategy, product pricing, technology transformation, and operating model design.

With over 10 years of experience, I have managed global teams to rapidly deliver results on time and within budget. My expertise includes improving sales functions, expanding products and geographies to support growth, redesigning operating models, executing cost synergies, and enhancing operational effectiveness, and launching sales campaigns. I employ a data-driven, hypothesis-based approach to problem-solving, with a strong bias for action.

In my career, I have overseen project timelines, executed complex transformations, and developed sales success strategies, particularly in technology-driven transformations across front, middle, and back offices.

I hold an MBA from NYU Stern School of Business and am a licensed CPA in both the Commonwealth of Virginia and the District of Columbia. Additionally, I am a Certified Fraud Examiner (CFE), hold an FMVA certification from the Corporate Finance Institute, and have a Chartered Alternative Investment Analyst (CAIA) designation from the CAIA Association.

Industries: B2B Technology, Enterprise SaaS, Fintech, Payments, Processing, Banking

Let‚Äôs connect to discuss how I can help drive your business forward.

email_text:
Dear Brandon, 

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a rising junior at NYU Stern studying finance and accounting, pursuing a CPA. I wanted to connect with you to learn more about your journey and your experience at Strategy&. As someone looking to start a career in finance, advice from someone with so much experience would be invaluable. 

I am particularly interested in understanding how a comprehensive digital strategy consulting firm is coping with the Fintech revolution and adopting new technologies. It would be insightful to hear about your experience in a field that pumps the heart of the financial world. 

As I start my career, I would greatly appreciate any advice and guidance you could offer. Your journey from a college graduate to becoming a leader in a top firm is impressive! I'd also love to learn more about the impact of Strategy&'s partnership with the International Institute for Analytics (IIA). 

I have enclosed my resume for you to look over. I would be more than happy to accommodate your schedule and find a convenient time to meet. I look forward to talking with you. 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

Expertise includes:

Deals
- Commercial and Operational Due Diligence
- Carve out and Standalone Analysis
- Sign to Close and Day 1 planning
- Value Capture and Operational Transformation
- Merger Synergies 

Consulting
- Growth Strategy
- Operations Strategy
- Supply Chain Transformation
- Network Optimization
- Strategic Sourcing

Prior experience in Investment Banking and earned an MBA from NYU Stern with  specializations in Corporate Finance and Operations.

Dear Sudharshan, 

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a rising junior studying Finance and Accounting at NYU Stern. I am just asking you about your availability for a quick call in the coming weeks to hear about your journey as a Partner at PwC and why you decided to focus on Strategy and Value Creation in M&A transactions from investments in Mechanical Engineering. 

As someone undecided on the best way to start a career in M&A consulting, advice from someone with so much experience would be invaluable. Your insight into the dual nature of diligence and the synergy capture process in consulting roles and why they are so crucial in deals to help value creation would be great to hear about. 

I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I am more than willing to work around your schedule to find a time that fits. I look forward to your reply and hope you have a great rest of your week! 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

sub_title: Partner at Strategy& | Energy & Natural Resources practice
summary:
Partner at PwC Strategy& (formerly Booz Allen Hamilton and Booz & Company), with 20+ years of experience in strategy consulting, after international experience formed in global companies.

Strategy consulting Partner role focused on business development, building long lasting client relationships, thought leadership, team mentoring, officer in charge of multiple projects.

Part of EMEA Energy, Utilities and Resources senior team. Current main focus on energy transition, gas assets, alternative fuels (LNG, CNG, H2).

Key skills developed through international projects in several business areas: from strategy & marketing to organization and operating model.

Relevant expertise in: new business development, strategy, project management, CDD, commercial optimization, operating model review and organizational design.

Key skills developed through 110+ international projects across 23 countries in Europe, USA, Middle East, Kazakhstan and South East Asia.

Responsible for HR, recruiting and staffing at Strategy& Italy.

MBA graduate at SDA Bocconi with an exchange at NYU Stern Business School.

Strong international perspective with 6 spoken languages.

email_text:
Dear Simon, 

I hope you're doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a rising junior at NYU Stern, majoring in finance and accounting. I am writing to ask about your availability for a quick call or coffee in the coming weeks to hear about your experience at Strategy& and why you decided to pursue an MBA at Stern after a career in strategy and analytics. 

As someone still determining the best way to start a career in strategy consulting, hearing your story and advice would be amazing. I would greatly appreciate the opportunity to learn from your experience and gain advice on how best to prepare for a career in strategy consulting over the next few years. 

I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that fits. I look forward to your reply and hope you have a great rest of your week! 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

summary: Currently working in the strategy consulting field focusing on corporate, customer and operations strategy. Previously worked in the retail space for 5 years focusing on business development, strategy and client relationship management.
