email_text:
Dear Shreya, 

I hope you're doing well and staying safe. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a rising junior studying finance and accounting at Stern. I'd like to know your availability for a quick call or coffee over the coming weeks to discuss your experience at Strategy and why you came to consulting from Imperial Oil. 

As someone unsure of the best way to start a career in strategy consulting, I would appreciate advice from someone with so much experience. I'd love to learn more about your experience advising the sale of Imperial Oil's retail business to Couche-Tard. 

I have attached my resume for you to look over. I am particularly interested in how Strategy& develops business strategies that are both environmentally sustainable and economically feasible. I'd greatly appreciate any advice you could offer. 

I look forward to hearing from you and hope you have a great rest of your week! 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

sub_title: Principal at Strategy& | NYU Stern MBA
summary:
I am a Principal at Strategy& (formerly Booz & Company). I am based in Dubai and operate across GCC countries. I have focused mainly on advising clients in the Digital/ Technology and Telecom space, working closely with senior management and leading work-streams on a wide range of engagements, including Large-scale Digital Transformation, Customer Journeys Design, B2C Business Planning, Customer Experience Optimization, Go-To-Market Strategy Formulation, Market Sizing and Forecasting, Organizational Restructuring, and Financial Planning.

Prior to being a strategy consultant, I worked as a technology consultant for 4 years on system implementation and process optimization projects in Singapore. 

I hold an MBA with Dean‚Äôs Honors from New York University - Stern School of Business, where I focused on Strategy, Finance, and Leadership & Change Management, and assumed several leadership positions as part of Stern Leadership Development Program and Stern Comedy Club (VP of Events). During my time in New York, I worked on a growth strategy project for one of LVMH‚Äôs premium whiskey brands, and as a board governance consultant to one of the oldest non-profit organization in the city. I also hold a Bachelors in Electrical Engineering (Honors) from National University of Singapore.

Functions: Digital Transformation and Technology, Growth Strategy, Customer Journey Design, Commercial Turnaround, Churn and Retention Management, Business and Financial Planning, Data Analytics, Predictive Analytics, Business Process Optimization

email_text:
Dear Ankit, 

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a rising junior at NYU Stern studying finance and accounting. I plan to ask about the possibility of a call to hear about your experience at Strategy& and why you decided to go into consulting after working in asset management. 

In particular, I'd love to know more about how you helped advise a non-profit organization like East Side House Settlement. As someone unsure of the best way to start a career in consulting, advice from someone with so much experience would be invaluable. 

I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I would be glad to work around your schedule for a call or meeting. I look forward to hearing from you and hope you have a great rest of your week! 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

Dear Beril, 

I hope you're doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I'm a junior studying finance and accounting at NYU Stern. Given your experience in HR and strategy consulting at Strategy &, I wanted to inquire about your availability for a quick call or coffee in the coming weeks. 

As someone unsure of the best way to start a career in HR consulting, advice from someone with so much experience would be invaluable. I'd love to learn more about your journey, from studying psychology at Hamilton to working in HR consulting. 

I've attached my resume for you to look at, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that fits. I look forward to hearing from you and hope you have a great rest of your week. 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

sub_title: Strategy Consultant at Strategy&, part of the PwC network
summary:
Working in the banking industry has provided me the opportunity to discover my talents and hone my skills of looking at the unknown, and then allowing my curiosity, intuition, and logic to find innovative solutions to complex problems.  With solutions at hand, I have often had to gain buy in from senior leadership and worked with cross-functional teams to implement my solutions.  Over the years, I addressed business challenges such how to forecast headcount and compensation at a large company, how to minimize costs to meet financial targets, and how to reduce business risk.  

As an NYU Stern MBA candidate, I have continued to improve my analytical and communication skills and learned frameworks that help address strategic challenges.  I have also assumed Leadership opportunities as VP of Alumni Affairs in the Langone Student Government; here I lead a team to plan large scale Alumni and Student Events.

Additionally I am a Board Member of the Indie Theater Fund where I strive to further the organization's mission of providing more grants that support independent theater year-over-year.

Specialties: Strategy, problem solving, consulting, communication, finance, operations, technology, cyber risk management, investments, data gathering and analysis, C-level reporting and presentations

email_text:
Dear John, 

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a rising junior at Stern studying finance and accounting. I would like to know your availability for a quick call or coffee in the coming weeks to discuss your experience at Strategy& and what led you to a career in healthcare consulting. 

As someone unsure about the best way to start a career in healthcare consulting, advice from someone with so much experience would be amazing. I'd love to learn more about your journey, especially transitioning from a BA in English and Communications to healthcare consulting. 

I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I would gladly work with your schedule to find a time that fits. I look forward to hearing from you and hope you have a great rest of your week! 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

sub_title: Manager at Strategy&, part of the PwC network
summary:
As a Manager at Strategy&, I bring over a decade of robust experience in management consulting, underpinned by an academic background in finance and strategy from Baruch College and NYU Stern. My journey in the corporate world began with a leadership development role, which set the stage for my extensive career in consulting.

Over the last eight years, I have engaged extensively with C-level clients, including CEOs, CFOs, COOs, CROs, and CIOs, across various sectors including financial services, consumer goods, healthcare, and technology. My work spans a diverse array of competencies: growth strategy, sales and marketing effectiveness, pricing optimization, operating model design, cost transformation, contact center transformation, regulatory strategy, process optimization, automation, CRM strategy, and cloud strategy.

Beyond my commercial projects, I am passionately involved in initiatives that address economic equality and social inequities. A testament to this is my pro-bono work with a New York City public high school, where I helped redefine their alumni engagement strategy. This project not only aimed to guide and inspire current students about their future aspirations but also stood as a reflection of my commitment to using my professional skills for societal benefit.

In my current role, my commitment is to drive high-impact solutions through a nuanced understanding of various industry challenges. Working with and leading diverse teams, I've honed my ability to manage and integrate different perspectives effectively. My experience in leading these varied teams has been pivotal in providing strategic, actionable advice to senior executives. My aim is to build strong, collaborative relationships with clients, steering them through significant transformations and fostering sustainable, long-term growth.

Dear Allana, 

I hope you're doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a rising junior at NYU Stern studying finance and accounting. I was impressed by your background in corporate strategy consulting, especially with Strategy&. I'd love to learn about your experience at the intersection of digital marketing and strategic foresight. 

I am particularly interested in how an MBA offers a versatile skill set for someone interested in digital marketing consulting. As someone not entirely sure of the best way to start a career in the digital economy, advice from someone with expertise in corporate engagement would be invaluable. I would like your thoughts on how traditional advertising firms adapt to this digital revolution. 

Would you be free to call or chat in the coming weeks? I would greatly appreciate the opportunity to learn from your experience and insights. I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I look forward to hearing from you. 

Have a great day! 

Pranjay Kumar

In my spare time, I enjoy writing, running, and debating the fine points of football history.

email_text:
Dear Kevin, 

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a Junior studying Finance and Accounting at NYU's Stern School of Business. I am just contacting you to ask about your availability for a quick call or coffee in the coming weeks to discuss your experience at Strategy& and why you chose to come from the creative side of Johns Hopkins to advise at a top-tier strategy firm. 

As someone still determining the best way to start a career in strategic consulting, advice from someone with so much experience would be excellent. I'd love to learn more about how you have seen the role of market analysis and media & entertainment strategy grow and change over the years. 

I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I would gladly accommodate your schedule to find a time that works. 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

sub_title: Strategy through Execution | Business Transformation Leader | Trusted Advisor | Healthcare and Technology
summary:
Trusted leader with more than 20 years of global consulting experience helping senior executives with their organizations‚Äô most critical transformative initiatives. Successful track record working with and advising leading firms of various sizes and structures across a number of industries with a focus on the Healthcare and Technology sectors. Results oriented relationship builder with the ability to collaborate, connect, and communicate with all levels of an organization, from Board and C-suite to junior managers, to gain buy-in and ownership for shared objectives, especially during times of transition and change.

Significant experience on topics from strategy through execution, including: 
‚Ä¢	corporate and functional strategy
‚Ä¢	operating model design
‚Ä¢	organizational effectiveness and restructuring
‚Ä¢	growth and efficiency improvement
‚Ä¢	M&A: commercial due diligence, merger planning and integration
‚Ä¢	designing, leading, and executing enterprise-wide transformation programs addressing talent, process, and technology dimensions

sub_title: Management Consultant | Advisory Board Member | MIT Sloan, Tsinghua, NYU
summary:
With over 5+ years of work experience in management consulting, strategy, tech, renewable energy and investment analysis, I am a passionate and driven management consulting professional at Strategy& (previously Monitor Deloitte and BCG). During my career I deliver projects for global corporate clients and governments. I have a strong background in business and finance, with an MBA from the Tsinghua-MIT Global MBA program and a B.Sc. from New York University. I bring diverse perspectives and experiences to the team, having worked and studied in different countries and cultures, and having participated in various initiatives and competitions in the fields of diplomacy, politics, and innovation.

As a management consultant, I work on projects involving strategy analytics, mergers and acquisitions, digital transformation, and cost-cutting for banking, insurance, payments, and fintech clients. I lead successful proposals, supervise analysts, present to the steering committee, and work with direct exposure to C-level executives. Some of the projects I have worked on include the CDD of a German tech company, the strategy for a public sector in one of the EU member states, and the digital transformation and cost-cutting program for a global insurer. I use my skills in investment analysis, leadership, and team building to deliver high-quality results and solutions for my clients.

Let‚Äôs connect: mateusz.moscicki@sloan.mit.edu

Shanghai's IAG is a sub-division of New York Stern Investment Analysis Group at 
New York University - Leonard N. Stern School of Business (http://www.sterniag.org). Since 1995 IAG has taught students the principles of investment and corporate finance. 

Our aim is to teach students about investment and corporate finance by introducing tools to make educated predictions and through peer and alumni lead instruction. 

The Investment Analyst Group seeks to be replicate the activities of a real investment group, in that students can independently research potential opportunities in financial markets across Emerging Asia.

Shanghai IAG develops the skills that allow to discern a smart investment from a bad one. IAG is limited to finance and business students, as the critical analysis, public speaking and quantitative skills that are developed are useful for any discipline, and the club will be a way for those who don't take that many classes in that area to gain some practical knowledge which is mutually exclusive with the classroom.

The Investment Analyst Group really seeks to build students‚Äô skills, where they can really apply their knowledge, rather than just be a platform for lectures. These practices were directed towards Jews, Poles, Sinti and others in Europe during the Nazi Germany era and Holocaust. email_text:
Dear Mateusz, 

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a rising junior at NYU Stern studying finance and accounting. I am just asking you about your availability for a quick call in the coming weeks to hear about your experience at Strategy& and why you chose to transition into consulting from several years in venture capital consulting and advisory at MIT. 

As someone still deciding the best way to start a career in strategy consulting, I find advice from someone with so much experience excellent. I'd love to learn more about Strategy&'s work in the aviation, energy, and financial services industries and how you see it adapting to the current COVID-19 global environment. 

I have attached my resume for you to look over. I'm very passionate about consulting and would greatly appreciate the opportunity to gain insights from someone with so much experience. 

I look forward to hearing from you and hope you have a great rest of your week. 

Best regards, 
Pranjay Kumar

sub_title: Strategist tackling public problems at Monitor Institute by Deloitte | Helping scale social impact and climate startup solutions
summary:
I am passionate about exploring unconventional ways to advance the public good through innovation, intra/entrepreneurship, and public policy.¬†Naturally drawn to contrasts, unlikely partnerships, and uncharted roads, I have conducted research, analysis, and strategy assessments in more than a dozen countries (from Europe to the Middle East and the United States).

I am currently based out of New York, where I help private, public, and social sector organizations solve complex public problems (particularly around strategy and foresight, social and civic innovation, economic and workforce development, systems change, and climate action) at Monitor Institute by Deloitte. 

Before joining Deloitte, I was a policy and strategy advisor to several public sector and policy stakeholders, including in the United Nations system and to regional and national governments, working to advance a more sustainable, equitable, and forward-looking vision of the world through education, diplomacy, and public-private collaboration.¬†

I graduated summa cum laude from New York University's honor campus in Abu Dhabi, following my time at United World Colleges (UWC Mostar, Bosnia & Herzegovina), and I was born and raised in southern Spain (Extremadura). If our interests or trajectories match, I would love to connect!

email_text:
Dear Mario, 

I hope youíre doing well. 

I am a junior studying finance and accounting at Stern, focusing on the CPA track. Given your background at Stern in Political Science and Social Research, I would like to know when you're available for a quick call or coffee in the coming weeks to hear about your experience at Monitor Deloitte and why you came to specialize in social impact and climate. 

As someone unsure of the best way to start a career in social impact consulting, I find advice from someone with so much experience excellent. I would love to learn more about the difference between working in social impact consulting and commercial consulting. 

I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that fits. I look forward to hearing from you and hope you have a great rest of your week! 

Best Regards, 
Pranjay Kumar

email_text:
Hello Cristian, 

I hope you're doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a junior studying finance and accounting at NYU Stern. I would like to know your availability for a quick call or coffee in the coming weeks to discuss your experience at Monitor Deloitte and why you came to consulting after doing Public Health at USF. 

As someone unsure of the best way to start a career in healthcare consulting, I'd love your advice. Your journey from Cognosante to Deloitte is impressive, and I am eager to learn from someone with so much experience. I would particularly like to know how you have seen the industry change during your time at Monitor Deloitte. 

I have attached my resume for you to look over. I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that works. I look forward to connecting and hearing from you. 

Best Regards, 
Pranjay Kumar

email_text:
Dear John, 

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a rising junior at NYU Stern studying finance and accounting. I would like to know your availability for a quick call or coffee in the coming weeks to discuss your experience at Monitor Deloitte and why you came to consulting from Lehman Brothers. 

As someone still determining the best way to start a career in strategy consulting, advice from an experienced professional like you would be invaluable. I'd love to learn more about your time at Stern and how you made the transition from Fordham to Stern. 

I would greatly appreciate the chance to speak with you and hear about your experience at Monitor Deloitte and why you came to consulting from Lehman Brothers. I am particularly interested in learning how you see the future of consulting post-pandemic and what advice you might have for someone just starting their career in the field. 

Please let me know if there is a time in the coming weeks that would work for you, and I will gladly work around your schedule. I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I look forward to hearing from you. 

Best regards, 
Pranjay Kumar

sub_title: Senior Leader | Helping Enterprises Achieve Growth through AI and Digital Transformation
summary:
Shakir is a leader in Deloitte's Business Strategy practice focused on Technology clients. He currently leads enablement of go-to-market alliance strategy and commercialization of artificial intelligence (AI) offerings. With a passion for bridging the gap between cutting-edge technology and real-world business impact, he helps organizations unlock the full potential of their AI investments. Shakir has a proven track-record of identifying target markets and positioning AI solutions from cloud to the edge to deliver measurable value

Prior to joining Deloitte, Shakir was a Business Transformation and Strategy Executive at Verizon, where he led strategic initiatives across Verizon Business Units, focusing on driving improvements in market performance for Verizon wireline products. He also spent 10 years at Accenture, leading strategic and complex engagements to transform and improve client functions. Shakir's mission is to help clients achieve their business objectives and create value through innovation, automation, and technology.

Dear Vincent, 

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a rising junior at NYU Stern School of Business studying finance and accounting. I would like to know your availability in the coming weeks for a quick call or coffee to discuss your experience at Monitor Deloitte and why you came to consulting from Utrecht. 

As someone considering a career in strategy consulting, advice from someone with so much experience would be invaluable. I'd love to hear about your experience and why you enjoy consulting. 

I have attached my resume for you to review. I will gladly work around your schedule to find a time that works. I look forward to connecting with you and hearing more about your journey. 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

Dear Dania, 

I hope you're doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a rising junior pursuing a BS in Business with a concentration in Finance and Accounting at NYU Stern. I am interested in learning about your experience at Monitor Deloitte and why you decided to pursue a career in consulting. 

As someone unsure of the best way to start a career in strategic consulting, advice from someone with so much experience would be invaluable. I'd love to hear about your work at Monitor Deloitte and your experience helping clients understand their most significant strategic challenges. 

Would you be available for a quick call or coffee in the coming weeks to discuss your experience? I have attached my resume for your reference, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that works. 

I look forward to hearing from you, and I hope you have a great rest of your week! 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

summary:
As a strategy professional, I enable client leadership teams to transform their businesses through data-driven choices as well as developing strategies to deliver sustainable growth into the future. As a trusted advisor, I unlock ways for clients to maximize their enterprise value by pinpointing where they should play and how they can win.

MBA graduate from NYU's Stern School of Business with a strong commercial and technical background.  Previous experiences include stints in corporate and business development professional as well as core chemical engineering with over ten years of experience in the energy space.

email_text:
Dear Nicholas, 

I hope you're doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a rising junior studying finance and accounting at NYU Stern. I would like to know your availability for a quick call or coffee in the coming weeks to discuss your experience at Monitor Deloitte and why you came to strategy consulting after completing your degree in chemical engineering. 

As someone still determining the best way to start a career in strategy consulting, advice from someone with so much experience would be beneficial. I'd love to learn more about your experience in transforming Lummus Technology's strategic vision and your journey from leading initiatives like carbon-free energy storage development to developing and selling new businesses across the globe. 

I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I look forward to hearing from you soon. 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

email_text:
Dear Paul, 

I hope you're doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a junior studying finance and accounting at NYU Stern. I admire your extensive experience in strategy and economics at Monitor Deloitte. Would you be available for a call in the coming weeks to discuss your experience at Monitor Deloitte and why you chose to leave the research world to pursue a career in strategy consulting? 

As someone still deciding the best way to start a career in strategy consulting, I find advice from someone with so much experience excellent. I'd love to learn more about how Stern's strategy and economics courses prepared you for such a career. 

I've attached my resume for you to look over, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that fits. I look forward to your response and hope you have a great rest of your week! 

Sincerely, 
Pranjay Kumar

Dear Marc, 

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a rising junior at NYU Stern, majoring in finance and accounting. I seek advice on starting a career in strategy consulting within the Media & Entertainment sector and would love to hear about your experiences at Monitor Deloitte. 

As someone unsure of the best way to start a career that combines my passion for finance and strategy, advice from experts like yourself would be invaluable. I would greatly appreciate the opportunity to learn from your experiences at Monitor Deloitte. 

I have attached my resume for you to look at, and I hope we can set up a time for a quick chat in the coming weeks. I greatly admire your accomplishments at Deloitte and would love to learn more about your journey. 

Thank you for your time, and I look forward to speaking with you. 

Warm regards, 
Pranjay Kumar

summary:
Sylu is a strategist who is energized by identifying and implementing innovative and data driven solutions for ambiguous challenges her clients face today. She has deep experience in helping clients articulate their vision for winning customer experience and developing actionable strategies and execution plans to deliver against that vision. She has worked with Fortune 500 clients across financial services, technology, consumer, travel & hospitality verticals. 

Sylu has a strong reputation for developing trusted advisor relationships with senior leadership, helping clients articulate compelling insights drawn from quantitative and qualitative analyses, managing high-performing teams, and delivering innovative solutions to drive growth. More than anything she enjoys empowering her teams to deliver their best while inspiring them to bring their authentic self to the workplace.

sub_title: Engagement Manager at Monitor Deloitte | NYU Stern MBA
summary:
I am a strategy consultant with over 9 years of management consulting and industry experience. I live in Dubai and work across the GCC. As an engagement manager at Monitor Deloitte, I work closely with client senior executives, and lead a wide range of engagements. Clients include ministries, government departments, regulators, investment authorities and funds.

I hold an MBA from New York University, Stern School of Business.

Previously, I worked for 5 years across a variety of investment advisory and hedge fund roles covering investing and trading strategies, credit derivatives, equity derivatives, currency pairs, blockchain based cryptocurrencies. Additionally, I worked for an investment bank advising strategic M&A buyers.

Functions: Investment Management, Economic Development, AI & Data Strategy, Digital Strategy, Digital Transformation, Innovation and Growth Strategy, Product Strategy, Customer Experience, Business, and Financial Planning
Skills: Project Management, Program Management, Strategic Planning and Implementation, Stakeholder Management, Public Policy, Financial Modelling, Valuation, Due Diligence, Market Sizing, Market Entry, and Feasibility Assessment

Dear Chris,

I hope this message finds you well.

My name is Pranjay Kumar, and I am a rising Junior studying Finance and Accounting at NYU's Stern School of Business. I am reaching out to inquire about your availability for a brief conversation or meeting in the upcoming weeks. I am interested in learning more about your experience at Deloitte and why you decided to pursue a career in strategy consulting.

As someone with no prior experience in this field, I am uncertain about the best way to begin a career in strategy consulting. Therefore, receiving advice from someone as experienced as yourself would be immensely valuable to me. I am particularly eager to understand more about your work in consumer goods M&A. 

I have also attached my resume for your reference. I am more than willing to coordinate with your schedule to arrange a convenient time for our discussion.

Thank you for considering my request, and I'm looking forward to getting to know you better.

Sincerely,
Pranjay Kumar
